Nigerian Breweries Plc has rewarded 374 trade partners and seven transporters at its annual Distributors’ Awards held in Abuja. At the award ceremony, which took place recently in the Federal Capital Territory, Ken Maduakor Group Limited emerged as the National Volume Champion and best distributor in 2021. Chrisemua and Sons Nigeria Ltd and J. Ogungbola and Sons Limited were first runner-up and second runner-up, respectively.  MDX Logistics was named the best transporter for the year 2021. The Managing Director, Nigerian Breweries Plc, Hans Essaadi, said the event was organised to honour and felicitate with partners for the excellent business relationship in 2021. The Sales Director, Nigerian Breweries, Uche Unigwe, appreciated the trade partners and transporters for what he described as their significant contribution to Nigerian Breweries success, especially in 2021. Speaking shortly after receiving the National Volume Champion award, the Chairman/CEO of Ken Maduakor Group Limited, Ken Maduakor, commended Nigerian Breweries for supporting its trade partners. . Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com